BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp
 -content/uploads/2026/02/Pitch-in-at-Hermann-Park-e1772040133699.jpg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/0
 2/Pitch-in-at-Hermann-Park-e1772040133699.jpg
UID:Y0xiTHgWbm_Ac59JIqtUD
SUMMARY:Pitch in at Hermann Park (CANCELED DUE TO WEATHER)
DTSTAMP:20260618T034735Z
DTSTART:20260617T083000Z
DESCRIPTION:THIS EVENT HAS BEEN CANCELED DUE TO THE WEATHER. \nGive the Par
	k you love a little extra care\, and help us get ready for the world! Join
	 us for “Pitch in at Hermann Park\,” a hands-on volunteer series where com
	munity members of all ages come together to help care for Houston’s most c
	herished green spaces. \nWe’re proud to work alongside FWC26Houston and Ha
	rris County–Houston Sports Authority in the Impact Houston 26 efforts to e
	levate the local environmental action on a global stage and build a lastin
	g\, positive legacy for our city. \nYou’ll work alongside Conservancy staf
	f on simple but meaningful projects like mulching\, planting\, and litter 
	cleanup — the kind of small efforts that make a big impact for visitors\, 
	wildlife\, and the health of the Park. \nThis volunteer session will be in
	 the Heart of the Park (6104 Hermann Park Drive\, Houston Texas 77030). Vo
	lunteers will meet at the Pedal Boat Kiosk. Enter through Lot G (near the 
	Zoo) or Lot E and park in Lot F.  Walk up the concrete sidewalk to the Ped
	al Boat Kiosk\, and we will be watching for your group. \nNo experience is
	 needed — just comfortable clothes\, closed-toe shoes\, and a willingness 
	to help. We’ll provide the tools\, guidance\, and a great way to spend you
	r morning outdoors while meeting new people and giving back to the communi
	ty. \nWhether you come with friends\, family\, coworkers\, or on your own\
	, your time truly matters here. Help us welcome the world to Hermann Park!
	 \nSIGN UP HERE. \nWeather:   Volunteer projects are rain or shine\, unles
	s there is severe weather. Cancellations due to severe weather will be sen
	t via text/email at least 1 hour before your shift. Use your best judgment
	 when traveling in inclement weather. \nQuestions? Email volunteer@hermann
	park.org or call 713-524-5876. Remember\, we are often out in the field\, 
	so email is the preferred method of getting in touch!\n\nhttps://hermannpa
	rk.org/event/pitch-in-at-hermann-park-12/\n\nFrom Hermann Park Conservancy
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/pitch-in-at-hermann-park-12/
LOCATION:Lake Plaza
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hermann-park
CATEGORIES:Hermann Park Conservancy
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
